    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Pike</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 219.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 4, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 15th of March, No.
                            157, has been received. The reaction of European opinion in regard to
                            the United States, which you have announced as having begun with the
                            success of Major General Sherman’s campaign, will doubtlessly be
                            accelerated by the intelligence which I have now the pleasure to
                            communicate, that Petersburg and Richmond this morning yielded before
                            the advance of Lieutenant General Grant.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Pike,</hi>
                                Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
